All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Controller
Controller class that acts as an intermediary between the Model and View classes.
Factory
The entry point of the vending machine application.
Items
This class represents the items that can be stored in a vending machine.
Items.Item
This class represents an item that can be stored in a vending machine.
Items.Item.ItemType
 
Items.ItemSlot
This class represents a slot in a vending machine that can hold an item.
Model
The Model class represents a model for a Vending Machine application.
SpecialVendingMachine
The SpecialVendingMachine class is a subclass of VendingMachine that allows the user to create a special vending machine with a base item and a list of standalone and addon ingredients.
VendingMachine
The VendingMachine class represents a vending machine that dispenses items and accepts payments.
VendingMachineDisplay
The VendingMachineDisplay class is responsible for displaying the items in a vending machine in a graphical user interface (GUI) using a JTable.
VendingMachineMaintenance
The VendingMachineMaintenance class handles maintenance tasks for the vending machine.
VendingMachineProducts
The VendingMachineProducts class provides a static method to add default products to a vending machine.
VendingMachinePurchase
The VendingMachinePurchase class facilitates the purchase process for items from the vending machine.
View
The View class represents the graphical user interface (GUI) for a Vending Machine application.
